text:
my hubby @bassandcomics bought a #music stand recently, as he's taken up learning the #bassguitar as an adult who didn't have a musical education, as a child. he's inspired me to dust off my #carnatic #southindian #classical music binder, where i painstakingly wrote the lyrics of songs for concerts in #tamil, back when i was 17! i could never memorise the words of songs, and this binder was my companion at every performance i gave. the music was what gave me a lot of strength in my toughest times.
.
.
written here are the words to a piece that always depicts the #festival of #navaratri for me. i began these 9 days of the #hindu #goddess by singing at the home of @chef_kanthi - the first time in decades that i somehow held the pitch and breath for a whole song. today, #saraswathipooja feels like a good day to share this page with you all. ğŸ¼ğŸ¶ with much gratitude to all those who have supported my journey, through tough ebbs and flows, and to those who have hurt me along the way too - every pain i felt in my heart, was a lesson. your encouragement keeps me going, even if i don't sing anymore. maybe one day, i will get back into it... ğŸ™ğŸ½ğŸ’•
.
.
like those in the #metoo movement, some things take time to open up about, we need to heal before finding courage to speak or sing. i too have faced a life before that on social media, one which was filled with tears & abuse. i stand with all those women who have found the words and platforms, to speak their truth! âœŠğŸ½
.
.
i'd love to see you illustrate #goddess #angayarkanni @meenatchigopal @uma.jeyaseelan @karthik12 @melovelyartist @the_legend_of_raj @gheehappy @ramesstudios â¤ï¸ğŸ¨

text:
does your organization have an internal complaints committee that redresses cases of sexual harassment of women at workplace? do get in touch with us here if you want to set one up and also undertake capacity building training of your employees at workplace. centre for social research is part of several organizations' internal complaints committee that includes private and public sector. to generate awareness leading to resolution and mitigation of sexual harassment at workplace, we undertake training on the same. the training requires minimum 3 hours and maximum of 16 hours for it to be effectively administered. we strongly recommend every organisation that has more than 10 employees to sensitize their employees on the law and the implementation. contact us to book a training. send a dm! 
in this picture is ms. kamlesh premi who has been with centre for social research for over 20 years and is on board of internal complaints committee with several organizations.

does your organization have an internal complaints committee that redresses cases of sexual harassment of women at workplace? do get in touch with us here if you want to set one up and also undertake capacity building training of your employees at workplace. centre for social research is part of several organizations' internal complaints committee that includes private and public sector. to generate awareness leading to resolution and mitigation of sexual harassment at workplace, we undertake training on the same. the training requires minimum 3 hours and maximum of 16 hours for it to be effectively administered. we strongly recommend every organisation that has more than 10 employees to sensitize their employees on the law and the implementation. contact us to book a training. send a dm! 
in this picture is ms. kamlesh premi who has been with centre for social research for over 20 years and is on board of internal complaints committee with several organizations.

one of the most common questions that arises about the #metoo movement is â€˜why now?â€™ as in, why wait til this moment in time to out a predator who harassed/assaulted/violated you ages ago?
this is a question which will divide opinions, irrespective of gender.
i think it is safe to say, that if you have never been sexually harassed ever, you will not be able to fully understand the shame and terror of the experience. this is not to say that people cannot be empathetic; they are, which is why our voices are now being heard, acknowledged and supported. 
but i donâ€™t know how to emote what that first unwanted touch feels like, and how you instinctively know that you will never be the same person ever again.
to say that you should have screamed or made a fuss or you should have reported him or that you should have put everything on the line and you should have done the right thing, is useless.
yup. you heard me right. if your argument starts with â€˜you should have....â€™ then youâ€™re starting off on the wrong foot.
if i could have, wouldnâ€™t i have done so?
if i could have. 
there must have been a reason, as paralysing or selfish or frightening or dirty or disgraceful as it might have been, but that one reason, whatever it is, kept me from saying what i should have said.
in my case, i was 22 and he was a member of parliament and held a place in the governmentâ€™s cabinet of ministers.
but letâ€™s flip the narrative shall we?
why is the first phrase out of your mouth, â€˜ohh you should have....â€™ instead of â€˜ohh he should not have...â€™?
dig deep, and ask yourself that question.
why did you put the burden of the crime, and yes, laying your hands on another human being when they have not given consent is a crime, on the victim and not the perpetrator?
when you answer the question about your motive for doing so, youâ€™ll have perhaps taken the first step to understanding why the movement sweeping the world is as much about you, as it is about me.

text: let's get to the core of the issue, make a real change that lasts! have constant follow-ups & keep the flame alive as the value system of our society forever! i see a lot of folks jumping on the #metoo wagon, the new happening thing in town! like we do for everything lets not make this just a big media circus, loads of channels & social media making the most of the momentum & then after a few months business as usual! all women should have a voice, be empowered, my main concern here is for us to be caught in this vicious cycle of empowering one gender, race, etc over the other, there will always be some folks who will feel neglected. let's break this cycle which constantly favours one over the other, bring people on the same platform of #equality, communication & #selfexpression. the fundamental issue between men & women is the way they are brought up, the influences, the deliberate ideas & views reinforced by important persons in their lives which consequently lead people to a certain behaviour as adults. there needs to be more #communication between men & women at a young age, to understand sensitivities, values, clear distinction between right/wrong. how each gender absorbs & processes information, behaviour is different yet so important to understand!  #strengthtraining #weighttraining #fitnessmotivation #fitnessmodel @pumaindia #pumahybrid #calvinklein #burberry #porsche #zara #beastmode #fit #crossfit #healthyeating #fitnessgirl #fitgirlsguide

text:
~flowers and thoughts~
.
through hurricanes, i sit.
pushing against 
the gushing winds.
red marks slashed 
across my back.
nails digging through
my skin.
.
i rake through 
your memories
as they begin to 
eat into my brain.
your hands 
against my chest,
breathing winters 
across my body frame.
.
sweet, sweet eyes,
made up of honey.
burning a hole 
through the muscles 
of my heart's agony.
your legs mount me
and i'm shivering inside.
my voice doesn't catch up
to the world outside.
.
i beg you
to make the cut.
to finish me off as 
i cry out my lungs.
but you keep going,
through the screams,
the bloody sheets
and the sweaty disgust
that flows with my tears.
.
now i stare at 
the ceiling.
i feel you move
somewhere deep. 
thumping my insides 
with a careless spree.
i move. 
like the bed 
i lie upon.
with eyes wide open
and lips too parched.
.
my soul is broken.
far more cracked.
thorns growing
in these wedges jagged.
flower, i was. 
pure and simple.
flower, i am.
torn and crippled.

and i am shivering inside.
my voice does not catch up
to the world outside.
.
i beg you
to make the cut.
to finish me off as 
i cry out my lungs.
but you keep going,
through the screams,
the bloody sheets
and the sweaty disgust
that flows with my tears.
.
now i stare at 
the ceiling.
i feel you move
somewhere deep. 
thumping my insides 
with a careless spree.
i move. 
like the bed 
i lie upon.
with eyes wide open
and lips too parched.
.
my soul is broken.
far more cracked.
thorns growing
in these wedges jagged.
flower, i was. 
pure and simple.
flower, i am.
torn and crippled.
_____ğŸŒ¸_____

chhinamasta: the one who sacrifices.
it is not as frightful as it may first seem and actually represents the spirit of sacrifice as the law of life, the law of evolution and the way of atonement on the path of karma. just as the sun pours forth its vitality, its rays of light and warmth in an endless sacrificial rite, so too the meditation on the form of chinnamasta deepens the capacity of the individual to surrender and share oneself with all. all the negative traits of nature are to be surrendered in the process.
she rules planet rahu and its effects and is considered as goddess parvati herself, who chopped her head to satisfy her attendants. .

text:
part 2 of 4
my family and i took my abuser to court.
we decided to use the truth and nothing but the truth to present our case, even if it meant the legal process taking the 4 years it did, as opposed to a quicker resolution with harsher, fictitious accusations. i had evidence and he knew i did. i still do. 
on the topic of evidence, iâ€™d like to put out there that until the day i left, i had no physical evidence of this abuse at all. i never spoke about what was happening to anyone â€“ not my family, not even my closest friends. i felt shame in the fact that someone i had chosen for myself was doing this to me. that i was failing miserably at this â€˜milestone relationshipâ€™ in my life. outwardly, it all looked hunky dory with dinners, movies and fun get-togethers with colleagues we had in common. i never took pictures because it didnâ€™t get to a point where there would be bruises. contrary to popular belief, not all bouts of physical violence lead to marks, bruises or any tell-tale signs.  i did let slip to my sister during a phone conversation one day that i was coughing violently during one of the fights but i never went on to explain to her that it was after he released his chokehold on me.  i did reach out to my abuserâ€™s family several times being at loss about what to do about this unfamiliar, hellish situation i found myself in. i got the age old â€˜adjust kar loâ€™, â€˜he is like this onlyâ€™& â€˜you must have somehow triggered himâ€™ in various permutations and combinations. mostly i got silence.
so after 8 months, i did what i could do. i left. and i took him to court.
the legal environment is unpleasant to say the least- court dates are months apart, judges routinely decide not to turn up to court and the routine line of defense against a woman is character assassination - photo copies of articles featuring me in vogue magazine as a brand/business owner were presented in court to argue that i was of loose character because i worked in â€˜feshunâ€™. this one makes me laugh till date. 
continued in my next post...
.
#metoo #timesup #totemhope #vaw #dv #feminism #india #strongertogether #powerful #womenforwomen #menforwomen #genderequality #

it is not as frightful as it may first seem and actually represents the spirit of sacrifice as the law of life, the law of evolution and the way of atonement on the path of karma. just as the sun pours forth its vitality, its rays of light and warmth in an endless sacrificial rite, so too the meditation on the form of chinnamasta deepens the capacity of the individual to surrender and share oneself with all. all the negative traits of nature are to be surrendered in the process.
she rules planet rahu and its effects and is considered as goddess parvati herself, who chopped her head to satisfy her attendants. .
.
.
.

text:
"women support women. everyone should respect each other. i respect these ladies, and i wish them all the best." - @therealkarismakapoor

that's how diva karisma responded diplomatically to the media's question about the current #metoo movement in #bollywood. i believe, due to their family background, karisma and kareena had no such experience unlike the fellow actresses. like i said earlier in my post, bollywood industry is cruel, fake and manipulative but not all the filmy people have been involved.

i personally encourage everyone esp. women to stand up for themselves and have the courage to speak and act against the sexual harassment in their workplace and society.

text:
part 3 of 4
i was also advised to tie my then long, wavy hair up and not to wear my spectacles to court because they made me look â€˜too smartâ€™ which would hinder my case as an abuse survivor. iâ€™m guessing common perception dictates that it could only have happened to you if you came across as a meek, cowering personality with a shaky voice, shivering hands and a general demeanor of defeat. i am far from any of those things and yet this happened to me. itâ€™s an uncomfortable truth but i implore you to open your eyes to the possibility of the truth that abuse is engrained in our species. if my experience helps even one of you to see things the way they really are then my job here is done. i have finished fighting this battle in court and been righted in most ways possible, many, many years ago, and so i have no reason to share any of this publicly - i only share it for you to take what you can from it.
our intent behind the case was as follows :
-	seek help from the system to ensure some form of justice. if people like me who have the means to use the system donâ€™t, we have no right to expect change in society. most people advised that i cut my losses, salvaged whatâ€™s left of my life and walk away. but letting him get away scot free without any consequence whatsoever would make me a part of the problem, and that didn't sit well with me. it would encourage him to abuse the next girl, and the next one, and even though most people would say that's not my problem, you know what? it is. this has been one of the best decisions of our lives and i stand here today, empowered and not silenced.
.
continued in my next post...
.
#metoo
#timesup
#totemhope
#vaw #dv #feminism #india #strongertogether #powerful

text:
part 4 of 4
-	show my abuser that there are consequences for any action â€“ good or bad. no sir, you cannot just get away with what you just did. it is not okay. and it is definitely not my â€˜karmaâ€™ (as i was once politely told by a member of his family).
-	other than the obvious loss of face for him, he would have to return all my belongings and compensate me financially (compensation for expenses i am not legally allowed to talk about). i did use a small amount of this money, rs.1600 to be exact, to neuter some stray dogs in my area! not meant to be symbolic of anything at the time, but it gave me quite a chuckle during some dark days.
itâ€™s been many years since all of this, and my life has long moved on to a very beautiful phase. i have the most wonderful, supportive and loving family that is the reason for everything that i am today. and a filtered down list of friends that truly had my back through it all. this is not my â€˜coming outâ€™ story â€“ itâ€™s simply something i felt the need to share for you at this time in the world. it is time for all of us to question what we say, how we act, and who we are in every sphere of our lives, starting from our homes. and in that spirit, i look forward to sharing more with you.
watch this space.
love,
atikaa
.
#metoo
#timesup
#totemhope #comingsoon #vaw #feminism #india #powerful #strongertogether

text:
dashmahavidhya 
chinmasta
5th shot
ğŸ“·Â© @harshit.photography .
.
.
chhinamasta: the one who sacrifices.
it is not as frightful as it may first seem and actually represents the spirit of sacrifice as the law of life, the law of evolution and the way of atonement on the path of karma. just as the sun pours forth its vitality, its rays of light and warmth in an endless sacrificial rite, so too the meditation on the form of chinnamasta deepens the capacity of the individual to surrender and share oneself with all. all the negative traits of nature are to be surrendered in the process.
she rules planet rahu and its effects and is considered as goddess parvati herself, who chopped her head to satisfy her attendants. .
.
.
.

text:
most women i know have a #metoo story of their own, and itâ€™s sad that so many of us have to go through what we have, just because we were born a certain sex.
.
the #metoo movement has been about many things: coming to terms with the past, warning other women, calling out perpetrators, and generally communicating that sexual harassment of any kind is not ok.
.
sure, not all #metoo stories might stand in court. not all #metoo stories might go to court. there will be abusers who will remain unaffected by the allegations. there will be cases where rape and sexual assault is confused with unsolicited male attention and advancements. there will also be a few men affected by their own actions when they were young and immature, who might not deserve the same punishment as more serious offenders.
.
but thatâ€™s the thing, the #metoo movement is messy, it is imperfect, because what constitutes harassment is subjective. and like a friend beautifully articulated, one cannot tell women to stop sharing their stories, when finally, now, they are able to. we need to be able to accommodate the movementâ€™s imperfections, just as we have been accommodating systemic misogyny all this while.
.
sure, the women speaking out now belong to a socio-economic class that has access to facebook and twitter, but that in no way invalidates the collective experiences of so many women, cutting across generations and professions, and the trauma each of them has had to deal with in their own ways.
.
the least we can do is be supportive to the women who are finally able to speak up, find their voice, and share their stories. you are not alone.
.

text:
#tbt ..... swagger bahurani!!!
.
well the picture has nothing to do to wat i have to say.... !!!
.
here s a ğŸ‘Š to all the uncles, mausajis, taujis, fufajis, neighbors, teachers, classmates, friends, officemates and all those men who thought women are their property and they can touch, grope, use... whenever and however they like....n we won't speak up bcz they think we r the weaker sex or they can embarrass us or they managed to scare us or whatever freakish reason they imagined in their head....!!!
.
gone is the time wen women kept mum...ur story is just waiting to come out in front of ur kids, ur wife, ur mother and the whole damn world so it's time for u to get scared!!!
.
i and i am sure each on of us has faced many such moments wen we felt awkward and unsafe wid ppl we knew and trusted and respected... it's hard to pen them down here not bcz i am ashamed but they are so many that there will be a serious space crunch....but i hope such ppl are now getting the hint that they can't take their crappy ways any further and i really hope our daughters don't have to face anything similar.
.
here's to safe future!!
.
.
.

text: with and without lashes. covered emotion vs not. i love me either way, now. but as do most, i have my fair share of insecurities. more than most know. it's important to let people know, especially those that are vulnerable, and idolize you, what makes you you as a person. i have been through so much. so much. i have been taken, drugged by a trusted friend, suffered through a miscarriage, struggled with an eating disorder for almost five years, and have been taken advantage of multiple times just for having a good heart. no one wants to know anyone's story. it's all surface now, because that's what we've narrowed ourselves into caring about. it's a sad world we live in. where lies and exciting stories have more face value than truth. where rumors run rampant and grow because the truth is uneventful and un-newsworthy. i can only hope the future is better than this. because if it isn't, just imagine how much worse it will be in the near future. so so so much worse. i weep for the children of our generation. #selfie #makeover #blondeshavemorefun #ombre  #have topostaprettypictobeheard #thereisaproblem #change #whynot #chickswithtattoos #chickswithpiercings #standup #metoo #wakeup #blueeyes #chameleon #loveyourself #united #nightin #seeme #househangs #letsfixthis #loveit #happy #smile #bedhangs #iamwhoiam #ifeelpretty #ohsopretty #neveraskingforit

text: this past month has been the hardest month to go through in about a year. for those who donâ€™t know i struggle with severe mental health problems and past traumas. this photo was taken a little more then a month ago about 3 days after having being sexually assaulted. things started to look up. but things took a sudden turn when i got sexually assaulted again by someone that i thought would be different but no. iâ€™ve been going to intense trauma therapy the past few weeks and it just disgusts me that people are like that in our world. this is not a cry for attention this is a cry for acknowledgment, that things like this do happen and should not be just â€œswept under the rugâ€ also this is a cry to fix our law system the when it happened a month ago i was told that i should not press charges by a, police officer, because he could press charges against me for the same charges that would be put against him. the most resent assault i immediately reported it and he got arrested not even a week later he was released and now he goes to my school. places that i thought were safe are no longer. people i thought i could trust i can no longer. when i reached out to the only people i could, (when the most recent time happened) they told me that i shouldnâ€™t have put myself in that situation. so please if any of you who have read this far, if i see something like this happen to anyone please stand up because one day it might be you... #metoomovement #metoo

text:
ğŸŒ¼ğŸŒ¼ğŸŒ¼
'cause i am not
a winged fairy
from your fairy tale
but a tigress
in the wilderness
in thorns and foliage
busy earning her stripes

they won't tell you
stories of me
'cause they are
terrified 
by the very idea 
of girls being
dangerously soothing

they are used to 
pretty pretty
and not pretty fierce
they have not gone
through hell
come out
gloriously scarred

they don't know 
what it is
to be
a perfectly-put-together mess
they don't know
how to love
a brutally loyal
wanderess

and when they gift you
scented pink roses 
and a bejeweled cage
tell them you are
the smell of earth taking showers
the touch of
name-not-known flowers

the taste of wild berries
the wind 
and the new books
and old libraries
how you can be
an irresistible confusion
exquisite imperfection

if they can't stand it
and are gone
don't you worry
the right one 
will have the heart 
to love you
as a beautiful oxymoron

love always,
aindriya

text:
20 women journalists back priya ramani, ready to testify against mjÂ akbar

mj akbar has been named in multiple accounts that have surfaced in the #metoo movement that started in india after former actor tanushree dutta accused her co-star nana patekar of harassment during a film shoot 10 years ago. 
union minister mj akbar's defamation suit names only one of the multiple women who have accused him of sex harassment, but 20 women journalists have pledged to testify in court against him.

the journalists, who worked with 'the asian age' --Â mj akbarÂ was editor of the newspaper for 15 years - put out a joint statement in support of their colleague priya ramani, the first to call out the minister for sexually harassing her during his years as an editor. she has been named as the sole accused in his lawsuit and has been accused by him of "intentionally putting forward fabricated allegations" to harm his reputation. "what akbar has demonstrated through his legal actions is his refusal to introspect, acknowledge or atone for his actions that have caused immense pain and indeed harm to many women over the years. he himself, in the meanwhile, continues to enjoy enormous power and privilege as minister and member of parliament," the journalists' statement said.

the journalists have urged the court to hear theirÂ testimonies against mj akbar, claiming that some of them suffered sexual harassment while others witnessed it.

priya ramani, they said, not only spoke about her personal experience, but also lifted the lid on the culture of "casual misogyny, entitlement and sexual predation" that akbar engendered and presided over at the asian age. "ramani is not alone in her fight. we would request the honourable court hearing the defamation case to also consider the testimonies of sexual harassment of some of us at the hands of the petitioner, as also of the other signatories who bore witness to this harassment," the journalists said in the statement.

#women  #treatthemequal #stopharrasement #girls #dontsettle ğŸ‘¿

text:
a year ago, my best friend @aasthaatray had a crazy idea. "let's make a podcast about love and relationships", she said. i was sceptical. "i'm gadgetwala, how do i qualify for this?" "you've lived and loved hard, you qualify", she said. 
anyone who knows aastha, will know that once she sets her mind to something, she makes it happen. our last episode out of 12 in season 1 of "love aaj kal" goes on @saavn today. it's about consent in the age of #metoo. 
as we wrap an incredibly satisfying season 1 and prep for season 2, i'd like to thank aastha. for everything. for inviting me on this adventure and for being the awesome inspirational person she is. no one's perfect, no one's always happy. but having honest conversations about issues helps. and that's what our attempt has been. if you've heard "love aaj kal", would love to hear your feedback. if not, the link is in my bio. give it a listen. it might be something you need to hear right now.

text:
when i was diagnosed with adhd at 19 years old i had just been raped and was dealing with police and prosecutors, iâ€™d moved cities/countries 4 times and dropped out of 4 universities and 1 college in two years, had a full-fledged eating disorder, was smoking cigarettes, was hopelessly in love with someone who would break my heart time and time again, and had no fucking clue what i was doing with my life.
.
thirteen years later iâ€™ve got 3 degrees, including a masters, am a proud feminist and have supported dozens of girls and women in their own trauma healing, i love my body, looooove good food, and ran my first half marathon a year ago, iâ€™ve reached my goals in one career and am thriving in my new tech career, i had an incredible, loyal, loving partner for 5 years who taught me what stability feels like, iâ€™ve traveled the world, developed a deep spirituality, overcome unhealthy use of drugs and alcohol, and have huge dreams for my future in so many directions.
.
some days i feel like iâ€™ve done nothing and gone nowhere in my life, but these are usually the days when iâ€™m comparing myself to other people or social standards. when i look at how far iâ€™ve come from from where i used to be, well, iâ€™ve swam the 7-seas and climbed the highest mountains. i still have a long way to go, and itâ€™s not often i take time to honestly reflect like this and give myself credit for how far iâ€™ve come. but right now, typing this, i feel proud of where i am, and of the strength and wisdom iâ€™ve developed along the way. so hereâ€™s to us, all the adhders making it out there in this big, crazy world. youâ€™re killing it and you deserve to feel proud. love u. .
.
.

once in a while an unsolicited email from a past patronage arrives in the inbox... and rather than delete it, you read it. 
this post is a result of such impulse: i read an email introducing a south dakota organization called â€œnative hopeâ€, and iâ€™m glad i did! 
sex and child trafficking within our country, (and internationally), is an atrocity which every citizen ought proactively partner against. 
after glancing at the context, how could i ignore or delete this email which presented me with an opportunity to partner in efforts against child and sex trafficking? 
i have talked about, read about, and listened to the disturbing reports pertaining to this issue within our country, (and globally), but tonight was my call to action as a citizen. there are many things that divide us in this nation and in this world. we become more polarized each year, but on this endeavor, may we unite as a people and together partner with dedicated organizations like native hope, to fight and end sex and human trafficking. 
thank you native hope and all organization  with this global and national mission!

text:
bedtime story folks. 
story by anonymous 
cw: non fiction, real life story. sexual abuse of minor. gaslighting and victim blaming.
year: 2007-2008 
imagine a girl in 6th grade . lets call her mia. her school has no scheme of sex education what so ever. 
now mia's school has this policy that a girl and a boy will share a bench. mia has always been a little aloof so she has only 2-3 friends in class. one day, the boy who sits next to mia- let's call him a- puts a hand inside her pinafore from the little gap kept for hooks. mia fumbles, and thinks that this happened by mistake. she ignores. the same thing happens thrice in the same day. 
she's afraid about facts being completely changed before they reach her friends or authorities. so she doesn't know if she should tell about a and what he is doing to her to anyone. this goes on for 4 weeks straight and mia doesn't reciprocate. . and in the time when she's staring into her notebook or she's talking to her 2-3 friends during pt class, a has told this story to at least 10 boys from his class. some have even seen it happen. and they have also seen mia shut up and not say a word. 
this goes on for a year. by then, a who used to just brush his fingers on mia's thigh has gradually moved steps ahead. he later started putting his hand inside her shorts and then inside her knickers and finally till her clitoris. grade 6, classroom, an 11 year old girl and a 12 year old boy stroking her clitoris. he also forces her to touch his penis and she refuses a lot. she's scared to talk to anyone. this boy threatens her that he'll tell about this to everyone so she does what he asks her to do. 
but at the end, it  messed up mia's grades, interests, hobbies, self confidence, self esteem and life then in general. she's afraid of having physical contact because whatever happened has left her shattered and scarred. 
this  story is from one of the so called prestigious schools of mumbai. all the names in the story have been changed because the writer doesn't want to be contacted.

text:
*** 10/16/18 update**** thank you all for sharing. willie emerson absolutely felt the pressure today and removed his facebook page. his son and his wife both heard from me and it seems to have him shook. this is just the beginning, so i need y'all to stay with me through this. i have to bring him to justice. who knows who else he has hurt. 
here is what i know so far. 
in 1993 there was a dcs case and trial that resulted in me being placed with my grandparents. after that, the system and the adults advocating for me failed tremendously. between my mom prioritizing her trauma over mine and my grandparents belief that you just need to "let go and let god", no pressure was put on law enforcement. fail!!!! too much to type out tonight.  just know if you are not vocal and staying on top of dcs, the sheriff's department and even the da nothing will happen. 
i am currently working with three different jurisdictions, so this is going to be a long ride. i appreciate the folks who have volunteered to help and give me their time and resources. i never thought that i'd be reliving this trauma as an adult. please keep sharing. do not let him get comfortable. share. tag friends, co-workers, employers, everyone. he is on borrowed time. 
#metoo #willieemersonisamonster #justice

should they be dismissed after a first offence? one strike and youâ€™re out.
should they be made an example of? 
should they be counselled? theyâ€™ve obviously got some deep-rooted mummy issues, right?
should they be given a slap on the wrist and told â€œnow donâ€™t do that againâ€? they have exceeded their sales targets for the past five years after all, it would a shame to lose them.
we need to engage individuals in order to bring about change.
the key here to solving this apparent chinese finger trick is to bring the issue itself to light. that is, talking about harassment in the workplace, its effect on others (not just those directly affected) and the organisationâ€™s attitude towards it â€“ change the status quo. and ensure this is followed through by every incident being taken seriously and acted upon.

text:
@regran_ed from @ecstatic_being -  and that is that. 
nothing more, 
nothing less. 
she is not running the race 
of being the best. 
don't tag her with supremacy. 
she doesn't want that. 
don't label her 
with a tag of being a weakling.
she can easily tear that.

don't challenge her stoicism
as she can push 
an entire human out from her system. 
don't express your fake devotion, 
by giving her a pedestal. 
don't worship her and call her a devi by morning.
if you beat her like devil the other night when she refuses to satiate your groins. 
don't question her promiscuity
if you can't honour the essence of your manhood and her divine beauty.

don't stop her from standing tall
when she is fighting 
against your pride so small. 
don't call her a prude if she is meek.
don't call her a "pseudo feminist' if she is a little rebel. 
and that is that. 
nothing more, 
nothing less. 
she is not running the race 
of being the best. 
she is just breathing 
and revering her being. 
being none less than a human, 
none more than a goddess.
.
.
-Â©charu madan

text:
we donâ€™t need more victims. we must stop the predators. join hands for a new movement to identify the predators. #youtoo 
you think your child is safe???? then read on....... #metoo is not just a hashtag for people to open up about sexual abuse that happened today, a month ago, 10 years ago or in their childhood. #metoo is a cry for help.. a scar that is never healed or will ever heal... it is people coming out with strong words, pointing out predators who we think our child is safe around.. so we can â€œprevent our childrenâ€ from more #metoo. 
clint stephen is my dear friend. his #metoo post surprised many because he disclosed some keys names on the post. those people we thought are the safest on earth. clint opened up because he got inspired by joseph mini thomas. so we thought only girls are abused and boys are safe because they are strong and no one will dare to abuse them? wrong!! child sexual abuse rate is higher among boys than girls. 
do you think what we really need right now is pulling out statistics and more and more facebook posts each day with people congratulating, arguing, shaming and waiting for more interesting stories??? no! what we need is prevention!! how can we bring a stop to this? 
we must join hands and raise our voice to bring more awareness on how to prevent child/sexual abuse. children and â€œparentsâ€ must attend child sexual abuse prevention classes. are you equipped enough to identify the predators? i met a 13 year old child who recently delivered a baby.. so who was the father of the child? her own father! 
#father #mother #grandfather #grandmother #brother #sister #uncle #aunty #cousins #friends #nun #priest #servant #fellowpassanger 
and the list can go on.. yes .. our children  are not safe. we donâ€™t need more victims. we donâ€™t need more survivors. say no to child sexual abuse.

text:
molecular dancer
hand-carved alabaster stone

the base is coming along... iâ€™m finally beginning to see how the back and sides will unfold. this part of the piece, the base, is a conglomeration of ancient goddess forms from throughout our ancestral past, rising up to hold the phoenix wing aloft. 
in process, a few more details and a few more weeks to go. 
this piece is meant as a trophy of triumph, a modern nike, presented to all women who have endured, (silently, painfully, sometimes with strength, other times with weakness, always courageously, and always without expressed informed consent) sexual assault.
it represents your futures beyond this era (that could end tomorrow or next year but certainly within your lifetime). it is the triumph that is inevitable for all women.

text:
this is a 1616 etching of pocahontas. 
our nasty president uses her memory in an attempt to denigrate senator elizabeth warren, but his cheap propaganda is misogynistic, racist and dumb. 
pocahontas was born to a native american tribal king. she was kidnapped by colonialists that were at war with her people. 
in a surprising turn, she married a british man and moved to england where she dressed in the latest frilly fashions and was paraded around as an example of a noble savage.

much later, disney portrayed her in a tight, skimpy dress and long, flowing hairâ€”a different kind of female role that our society deemed attractive, acceptable and nonthreatening. was it an accurate account of the real pocahontas? 
there is no doubt that she had an incredible story to tell, but it is unclear whether pocahontas was able to fully express her truth. did she ever experience freedom? equality? self actualization? acceptance from society? 
with this 2.25-inch pin, we begin to restore and honor the life and epic story of pocahontas. we also honor senator warren, for busting doors and talking over the men that seek to silence her. 
nevertheless, women persist.
link to shop in profile.

text:
"it is angering that akbar is now fighting a young woman with a criminal defamation suit. criminal defamation that every journalist has been fighting against as misuse of the law. to use the bludgeon to swat a butterfly just shows the desperation of the attacker. and makes it imperative that he be acted against. i do not expect the bjp to do so, but i do think all others in and outside the movement can unite to ensure that the case is dismissed by the courts, and no such cases filed against the other women in the list of complainants. even now akbar can do the right thing for once, by resigning and then fighting defamation if he still feels after honest introspection that he has been wronged. he just might find himself convinced otherwise," writes seema mustafa

text:
.. the lies we tell ourselves of
bartered dreams and mercable hearts;
.. rumors to spread through closed curtains,
studded with our faulty stars.
.. the faith we nurture ourselves from
black hopes and wilted ends;
.. adorn the flesh with tattooed sins,
sabotaging voices of the screaming scars. ..
..
the curses we bless ourselves with
moaning smiles and deafening laughs;
.. rains to devour the wintery spring,
how many seasons more for truth to come?
.. the lies we tell ourselves of
sweet fiasco and obscene melodies;
.. stalked by owned shadows at ungodly hours,
tales of past to clatter away with sunup.
..
..
..
//true lies, all lies//
|
|
|

.. the lies we tell ourselves of
baered dreams and mercable heas;
.. rumors to spread through closed cuains,
studded with our faulty stars.
.. the faith we nuure ourselves from
black hopes and wilted ends;
.. adorn the flesh with tattooed sins,
sabotaging voices of the screaming scars. ..
..
the curses we bless ourselves with
moaning smiles and deafening laughs;
.. rains to devour the wintery spring,
how many seasons more for truth to come?
.. the lies we tell ourselves of
sweet fiasco and obscene melodies;
.. stalked by owned shadows at ungodly hours,
tales of past to clatter away with sunup.
..
..
..

text:
humble request : it will only take few moments to read the story below.ğŸ˜Š i came across a story of a girl who was leading a normal life like most of us. one sunday she went out with her best friend for a walk. she knew him for like 4-5 years. while walking she didn't realise that they have come to a deserted place. he all of a sudden groped and manhandled her,she was left in shock, she couldn't figure out what was going on. she was fortunate enough to escape. even though she escaped but that incident stuck to her mind so hard that it affected her personality in one or the way, she couldn't trust people anymore, she became less confident.

people are speaking in favour as well as against #metoo movement but here who was at fault. the guy who must have thought that if she is coming with me for a walk then she will also allow me to harass her or the girl who went for a walk with a guy whom she knew for 4-5 years and trusted him. such incidents are small but they leave a long lasting impact on a girl. it's your choice to choose a side. 
leave your verdict in the comment section and thank you for reading it

ps : if you keep giving more and more air to the fire, it will burst outâš¡

text: thank goodness our society is recognizing the importance of sharing our stories and being heard and believed by others. but what about the importance of being heard and believed by ourselves? many of the stories we have told ourselves for years have crystallized into predictable patterns. but we have grown and hopefully developed a more nuanced approach to life. it takes courage and humility but when we dare to examine our old stories with fresh eyes, it can be like hearing these stories for the first time. and if we dare to believe this new interpretation, the story itself may not change but we will. i created the photo collage you see here after having had just such an experience this week. #ibelieve #metoo

stop it at the start aims to help break the cycle of violence by encouraging adults to reflect on their attitudes, and have conversations about respect with young people. "while not all disrespect ends with violence, the cycle of violence certainly starts with disrespect," minister for women kelly o'dwyer said. "it's good to remember that our behaviour is a powerful influence on others, particularly the young. "throwaway comments like 'it's just boys being boys' or 'he did it because he likes you' can make young people think disrespect is a normal part of growing up. we need to ask ourselves â€” is that what we meant?"

text:
i remember sitting across from two police officers at the station just four hours after my assault. i wasnâ€™t able to wash, to change or to eat anything until after the examination that was scheduled for three hours later.
i sat in a building where my attacker also was
.
recounting the details that i could recall. trauma and panic had erased some of them. their first sentence to me after i told them my story was â€œyouâ€™re luckyâ€
.
i wanted to jump across the table at them. i was enraged
.
i was not lucky
.
i was assaulted. do not downplay that. do not excuse that. do not invalidate my trauma
.
this book really resonated with me. it validated those feelings of rage and helplessness. it allowed me to heal and i hope it will help us all to change how we see and hear survivors
.

text:
for me, the difference of being a survivor over a victim lies in the way it affects you. a victim mentality is tempting to stay there for multiple reasons. one, you get sympathy from others which is a form of energy that you can feed off. two, a victim mentality can be a fallback for responsibility. i used carry a victim mentality before i was aware of it to be fair. i legitimately used to look forward to telling people about the negative things i had been through to get their pity. but that was 17 year old me who didnâ€™t know any better ğŸ¤·ğŸ¼â€â™€ï¸ you see these types of people commonly, they are the people who tend to share bad news after bad news after bad news. that doesnâ€™t necessarily mean you canâ€™t tell your story, itâ€™s just that your sense of self no longer identifies with those traumas. you share with the intention to have others relate and know they arenâ€™t alone as opposed to what you get in return. you no longer rely on those situations to get energy from people. 
a survivor thinks in such a way that is not â€œwhy does this all happen to meâ€ but rather â€œwhat lessons did i need to learn from this that is in alignment with my purpose?â€. survivors use it to grow and to learn discernment. we donâ€™t let these traumas make us bitter but better. you can either let it eat you up and become what killed you, or use it to become the opposite. 
many times my heart has been ripped from my chest. beaten, stomped on and burned against my will. but i refuse to have anything less than a heart of gold. 
i have two other rape stories that i have endured that maybe i will share later on. in the end i have used every trauma in my life to bring me closer to source. life tests us time and time again, and itâ€™s up to us how we let it affect our lives. 
thank you all endlessly for the support on my last post. iâ€™m currently starving about to have dinner right now so my brain is not working 100% ğŸ˜ iâ€™m not going to be able to get back to you all individually and i hope you can understand. ironically enough i feel heartless saying that but the love and support does mean everything. iâ€™ve always said vulnerability is the weapon of the future and now iâ€™m really seeing why. thank you. â¤ï¸

text:
we don't always understand until we have had experience, like this quote that i didn't understand until i had a realization about my life. abuse comes in many forms and recognizing abuse is not always as simple as you might think, when you think that you deserve to be treated a certain way and you live it everyday that becomes your reality, and sometimes you have no idea that anything is wrong. healing and awareness come from personal growth when you start to know your own worth. i used to think it was normal to only be shown love after i had been hurt, i became so incredibly alone that i was desperate for love. i had to learn how to love myself. i was killing the bird. abuse is not always visible, it is always masked by a performance. 
i am awake. i am alive. i am still fighting.
#metoo #abuseawareness

text:
inspired by the strong women around me to share some thoughts...
.
the man â€œwith the golden touchâ€ people used to say, referring to his musical talent. hearing those words used to make me feel sick, knowing that those same hands touched me.
.
as the carnatic #metoo movement unfolds, iâ€™ve sat here holding on to my story. conversations about speaking up and reporting hit home as i recall why it took me nearly three years to tell my sister, parents, and dance teacher what happened to me.
.
what i remember more than anything is how those around me responded â€” the ones who stood near me at dance events to make sure he didnâ€™t come close by, the ones who let me call every time i received a message from him, but also the ones who didnâ€™t believe me, who teased me by mimicking the incident, who made me feel guilty for ruining his reputation and opportunities, and who said he would be chosen over me in my dance school. these interactions had a lasting impact on how i processed my own experience, my value, and my self-confidence. i came to believe that strength and grace meant forgiving and forgetting with compassion, sitting quietly while he accompanied well-known dancers, and keeping my story to myself.
.
each time someone shares their story, it takes an immense amount of courage and trust which should be met with support, love, and comfort. while itâ€™s of utmost importance that the abuse, the assault, and the subsequent silencing of these incidents stop now, itâ€™s critical that teachers, parents, peers, and friends know how to respond in positive and empowering ways. your response has the power to lift someone up or make them feel small, and your words and actions stay with us for our lifetime.
.
thereâ€™s so so much more to say. if you need someone to talk to, please donâ€™t hesitate to reach out to me. â™¥ï¸
.
forever thankful to some of the people who are and were my sources of support @etdoshi @ninavir @tj0sh @nikitaraoo @mythiliprakash @arthsandcrafts

all throughout my childhood, i tried to understand what made my dad suddenly start hating & targeting his abuse towards me as i grew older. it finally made sense. i self medicated with alcohol & promiscuity & got myself into a lot of trouble during that time. i let myself lose my job due to poor attendance from not being able to deal. let my guard down & got roofied at a bar i had been to dozens of times & reported my car stolen the next day because i didnâ€™t have any recollection of where it was after being drugged. put myself in dangerous situations where i could have easily been text:
our aunt barbara, wife of the man who we all adored uncle thomas â€œtommyâ€ maratea jr. (son of thomas mararea sr. and lucy siano) is very sick and in hospice care. prayers for her peace and serenity are appreciated. 
i would defend this woman with my life for how happy she made my uncle tommy and for all the roller coaster ride experiences we shared with her struggle with schizophrenia and mental illness that helped shape who i am today. sheâ€™s been in my life since i was 7 or 8. 
sheâ€™s a kind soul and tries her best with what sheâ€™s been dealt.
personally, i believe barbara is a survivor and her smile, in spite of all sheâ€™s been through, is angelic and real.
barbaraâ€™s #metoo story is tragic with constant sexual abuse by her father. i believe that, like many other women at the time in a world that hid abuse of women by locking the victims away, her ptsd from the trauma landed her in an institution and experimentation and abuse continued from there. whether her treatment was the cause or the cure of her illness is a question i often ask myself about her. 
thank goodness she found my uncle and had almost 30 years of joy and love.
barbara is such a shero to me, i donâ€™t think she truly understands how much i admire her courage to endure and stay positive.

this is a norm here in pakistan, rishta (marriage proposal) always come from groomâ€™s side, they appear at girlâ€™s place on a hi-tea, to investigate her, her family, lifestyle, habits, house etc etc. first the groomâ€™s family judge girl on her looks, height, color, physical appearance, education, skill set, parents financial state. usually a girl is rejected at this stage but just in case she is approved, they does â€œistakhara(religious way to get allahâ€™s approval in dream)â€ which almost all the time come a no as the groom has multiple options.
.
.
theyâ€™ve the upper hand and power of making final decision to approve or reject a girl without letting their son meet with girl or her family in all this process who cannot be a match for girl even.
.
.
if the girl is rejected by groom and his family, rishta spree continues in several other houses by groomâ€™s family for more hi-tea options and girlâ€™s parent search more losers to invite over. if the girl is approved, they allow groom to meet for few minutes under tight supervision.
.
.
just in case there is an â€œyesâ€ from groomâ€™s side, the girl has almost no choice but to say yes because sheâ€™s one in million whoâ€™s finally selected. parents almost not check, and if check they ignore the bad qualities of groom. why? because you donâ€™t find good rishta everyday.
.
.
if girls with high education, pretty faces, bright careers and heavy self confidence keep rejecting the unmatched rishtaa, they remain cursed by society and ultimately need to settle with an unknown guy.
.
.
you canâ€™t seek respect from a relationship which is started with this disrespect? why girls canâ€™t work on their self esteem, confidence, appearance and education and get the power to say a no and select what is better for them, themselves, even itâ€™s late.
.
.
girl, this is high time to change. never settle for less, empower yourself that you approve/reject people. and, oh yes this society will come in your way telling that youâ€™re getting overaged, ugly, your fertility will go away in few years but keep your head high and gathers the energy to give everyone a shutup call.
.

text: hey all, i did a thing. i launched a t-shirt fundraiser campaign through @bonfire. i chose to make a shirt that is not your average "awareness shirt." raise your hand if you have a drawer full of awareness shirtsğŸ™‹ğŸ½â€â™€ï¸ there's nothing wrong with those shirts, they serve a purpose, but we all have enough of them. i wanted to design something that was fun and could speak to all women's journeys. the #metoo and #ibelieveher movements have shaken things up, but more than anything they've shown us how much we all have in common. i wanted to design something that we could all embrace, so here you have it ğŸ’œ "we are the granddaughters of the witches they could never burnâ€ ğŸ’œ this quote reminds me that we are born out of adversity and our strength comes from the fires we live through. also, this was designed by me. i spent nearly a decade doing graphic design, communication and special event work. it's been a hot minute, but i wanted to make something that not only spoke to the strength of my journey, but was also f-u-n to wear. no matter what we're facing, we are survivors and we are stronger when we come together to support one another. i believe in your journey and support it. i hope you will stand with me as well ğŸ’œ can't afford a shirt? share the link in my bio! ğŸ’œ on december 19, 2018 i will be undergoing surgery to treat congenital abnormalities to my spine. in 2014, i had a similar surgery, but i also lost a part of my skull and brain. i need approximately $8,000 to make this surgery and recovery a reality. at the time of creating this our community has raised $1,200 to help me with surgical costs. ğŸ’œ i have a congenital skull malformation called #chiarimalformation. my entire life i have lived with a long list of debilitating neurological symptoms that have shaped my ability to function. diagnosed at 15, it wasn't until i was 34 and my symptoms were life-threatening that i found a specialist who understood how to best treat me. in 2014, i underwent brain and spine surgery to create more room in my skull and at the base of my spine. it worked! i started having new symptoms this year and in july was told i need another surgery. #chiariwarrior #spoonielife

text:
forgive and forget? | october 18 | hss 154

as a result of louis ck's recent return to the limelight, we will be discussing the #metoo movement and how former abusers are considering re-entering their workplaces. though rehabilitation appears to be a viable option in the face of abuse, the workshop will focus on how the language surrounding "forgiveness" is focused on ultimately silencing the victims. 
capitalism kills | october 23 | smc quad

as a part of sustainability week, we are going to be hosting a mini-workshop on the relationship between capitalism and climate change. though most conversations regarding sustainability and environmentalism place blame on individual consumers for waste, ifa wants to explore the role that corporations play. join us for discussion and games!

club row | october 25 | smc quad

visit us at club row! we're gonna have candy, games, information on future events, and more candy.

cultural appropriation as a lifestyle | october 30 | hss 151

although conversations regarding cultural appropriation pop up around halloween, these conversations tend to die once november 1st hits. we wanted to explore how people will utilize cultural appropriation to promote their platform, agenda, or career. though the intentions are typically not malicious, the workshop will explore how this contributes to existing hegemonic structures.

today i had a very â€œwokeâ€ discussion with coworkers about the reality of being a woman and the necessary precautions women are expected to take to ensure their safety. for as long as i can remember, my mother taught me to always be on guard: to never walk in the street by myself after dark, to make sure my car always had gas (to avoid needing to stop at a gas station at night by myself), and to be ready to protect myself if necessary (sheâ€™s been asking me to take self-defense classes for years). fear was instilled in me from a young age, and although it wasnâ€™t always as direct as my motherâ€™s advice (sometimes it was subtle like my brother buying me pepper spray to keep on my keychain â€œjust in caseâ€), this fear, this expectation, became a part of my norm. it became a part of my daily life, and as of late, my daily struggle. i feel both disappointed and infuriated that i will likely need to give my own daughter the same advice, and i also feel hopeful that i can use an open forum like ig to discuss sensitive topics such as sexual assault and our personal experiences with the wrath of gender inequality. iâ€™m curious to know thoughts from both men and women about this topic â€” what do you all think?

but more so than that... i can't even begin to understand these women who defended him and gave his narrative a wink, nod and loyal pass of approval??? and while i'm not trying to shamelessly promote and tie my upcoming song release into this cra cra... this ğŸ’© right here is exactly why i wrote my new single "brand new day" cause, we need one. whatever kind of sick consciousness this is, on both sides of the gender aisle, has got to be slayed. this along with other people injustices catches my radar strongly and whatever part i play in the shift.. i'm fired up and ready to go. but again, how in the world does any women, one whose loins is honored to birth children and especially daughters into this life--how tf do they just sign off on this kind of bat crazy lunacy. supporting a man who says he could throw a woman down to the ground and rape her if he wanted cast both he and them into the land of the lost .. truly those women are an enemy to thine own self.  oh my god to know that there are scores out here, women like these walking around, those who are allied with keeping women as a whole, oppressed and subservient ...and to know that many of them will be voting in this upcoming election just chills my sensibilities to the deepest part of its core. clearly many are saying one thing but in secret will do another? no matter how you slice it up...this is some seriously scary shenanigan shit right here. yeah, they say we've come a long way baby... but oh lord , knowing this mentality in women hugely exist means those of us caught up in unloosing the struggle are in for a long trek ahead. now i gotta go do some yoga again (2nd time today) to get this bullğŸ’©off of me sighğŸ˜±

text:
what's the definition of brave?

dictionary definition: possessing or exhibiting courage or courageous endurance.

i've been asking myself, how have i been brave? i was brave when i left my abusive husband. i was brave when i started my life over from scratch. i was brave when i fell in love again. i was brave when i reported my rape and went through the court process. and i am brave everyday when i face my struggles with my mental health.

i like the term courageous endurance. i interpret it as having the strength to make tough choices and decisions, as i stated above, everyday. as survivors we are brave. remember that on the days where you feel weak and overwhelmed.

text:
review
not knight approved ğŸ‘ğŸ¾ğŸ‘ğŸ¾!! keeping in mind that i was never really a fan of the original charmed, i can still say that this version is worse and it was really cheesy. though we as an audience have come to expect to see the most beautiful people on earth solve problems on the cw this one doesn't have the charm that flash or riverdale carries. iâ€™m not one of those people who demand a remake not happen or that it literally be a clone of its predecessor. but i do ask that the heart that made the original good is still showcased. for example â€a star is bornâ€ did that brilliantly this year. although that's a lot to be compared to it doesn't take away from how ingenuine this pilot was. everything was poorly executed. from that weird white walker villain, to the mystery surrounding macy being given away, to the god awful me too representation forcibly inserted in. my biggest problem was the lack of chemistry between the leads. these three don't at all feel like sisters or even friends. iâ€™m so aware they're acting it's painful. all flavor from the original has been lost. i have absolutely no clue what this show was trying to say or who the target audience is because i didn't believe a single person can watch this and want to move on to episode 2. it's corny of me to say but charmed has zero of it. dear cw, though im sure you had great intentions, you can't just throw a gorgeous cast at a reboot and a mediocre script and call it a day. #charmed #witch #sisters #tv #review #magic #reboot #cw #flash #riverdale #sorority #college #metoo #gameofthrones #cold #demon #dog #three

@regran_ed from @rachel.cargle -  weâ€™ve gathered over $20,000 in 24 hours.

this is tangible action based community support.

this is intersectional feminism beyond marches, signs and pussy hats.

this is citizen led redistribution of wealth.

this is powerful.

text:
i try not to spill my problems on to the internet, but the past month has been a real struggle for me mentally after a really traumatic experience (also not a first for me, but it definitely triggered underlaying anxiety that was already there).
iâ€™m not quite ready to talk about it, but iâ€™m thankful for the support system i do have (looking at you @bryanstrittmater, @trashflavored_trash, @katenevold, @katiebugg5, @itsbees, & @ttormoen to name a few). this is a video i took on the down swing of a panic attack i had this past weekend. 
i think personal struggles are so important and can define who you are as a person. i personally struggle so much with reaching out when iâ€™m in that bad place, but i allowed myself to actually be vulnerable for once. when iâ€™m in the middle of a panic attack, most of the time music is the only thing that can calm me down while i lay in bed, usually bawling my eyes out, until iâ€™m able to get myself to the level that my brain can somewhat function again. 
if anyone is struggling and needs someone, iâ€™m always an open ear, regardless of the shit on my plate. we all have our days and i know how hard it is to truly be open and vulnerable, so just know iâ€™m always here if you need it. ğŸ–¤
.
.
.
.

text:
iâ€™m not one to get political... but after many conversations over the last year about the #metoo movement and now with the recent brett kavanaugh / dr ford senate hearing, i have a proposal. letâ€™s stop and take a second to actually listen to one another, no matter how much they differ from your opinion.

iâ€™m sure we can all agree that there has been a disparity of power between men and women for a long time- i donâ€™t know any woman that hasnâ€™t dealt with or known someone that has dealt with sexism or abuse on some level. has the movement gone too far- maybe at times, yes. but rather than live in the divide perhaps we can create a bridge. i had the privilege of sitting with 3 influential individuals who were on different sides of the spectrum and we had an open, honest, raw and real conversation. it wasnâ€™t democrats vs republicans, it was 4 people who wanted to understand and come up with solutions all while showing empathy, respect and love for one another. these are the kinds of conversations we need to be having. this is how we can unite rather than further the divide. this is a defining moment in history - what are we going to do about it?
â¤ï¸
@alyshiaochse @itsrobnelson & @talktometaylor -thank you for being open and authentic and sharing your beliefs. interview in bio ğŸ™ğŸ»

text:
disclaimer: (this is not at all my opinion, but is an assignment for a debate in class). the film industry is a more beautiful place with diverse characters and actors, but recently it seems like hollywood is forcing diversity over the quality of the actual story. there are cases where directors have seemingly forced their characters to be very diverse and had negative effects on the movie. this was present in ava duvernayâ€™s recent film â€œa wrinkle in timeâ€. this movie stressed casting diverse characters including oprah, storm reid, mindy kaling, andre holland and gugu mbatha raw. these are all great actors and people, but it seemed as if duvernay, a very successful african american director focused too much on casting diverse characters, rather than developing an effective story. this film flopped in the box office and received many negative reviews. this subtle change of having more diverse characters in hollywood has also led to great films though including black panther, crazy rich asians, coco and lady bird. these films focused on developing their story to its full potential before casting their characters. the only way hollywood will continue to become more diverse is through very successful films and â€œa wrinkle in timeâ€ is just one example of a movie that took on this challenge and failed. also, the top three grossing movies of all time are avatar, titanic and star wars:the force awakens. these movies had very little diversity and managed to become some of the most successful movies of all time. to summarize, what i am trying to say is that diversity is good for movies, but not when it is forced as a way to try to make money. 
#ecstorytellers #film #diversity #metoo

text:
@madeinblackamerica  brittany "b.monÃ©t" fennell is a writer/director who graduated from spelman college
with a b.a. in english. she hails from silver spring, maryland and holds an mfa from
new york university in film and television with a concentration in writing and
directing.
in her films, she poses questions about identity, society, race, and culture. it is vital to
her that under-represented people are shown in film, media, and television.
her award-winning short film q.u.e.e.n. has screened at over a dozen of festivals
including cannes short film corner and premiered on magic johnson's channel
aspire. additionally, she was a runner-up in the first time female filmmakers
contest with women and hollywood. 
she was also named the 2017 horizon award winner through cassian elwes, christine
vachon and lynette howell - taylor at the sundance film festival. as well as a
recipient of the adrienne shelly foundation grant and a directing fellow for film
independent's residency program project involve.
additionally, she is one of the winners for the #newview film competition with
glamour and girlgaze which champions the voices of female filmmakers. she is also
one of the filmmakers in the tisch other showcase that focuses on diverse artists
whose voices are underrepresented in the television industry.
recently, she directed a branded short film entitled sheâ€™s revolutionary on the
#metoo founder tarana burke for leviâ€™s and girlgaze.
b.monÃ©t won the 2018 best graduate feature screenplay for her feature film
q.u.e.e.n. she is a recipient of the will & jada smith family foundation grant at
fusion film festival as well as a finalist in the women in film mini upfronts program
and a sundance womenâ€™s financing intensive project fellow for her first feature film

text:
i have failed at times as a daughter,  a wife, a nanna, a girlfriend, a mum and a friend. i'm not perfect ! i don't always say or do the right things. i don't have an amazing body (i do try to work at that - but not everyone likes my muscles). i'm not the most beautiful woman in the world, but i'm me. i love healthy food. i love chocolate,  i love vodka & wine & a good cup of tea and now i'm passionate about my life changing stiks ğŸ˜  i have curves. i am dedicated to my work and i have many many scars because i have a history. some people love me, some like me, some don't. i have done good. i have done bad. i sometimes go without make up and sometimes don't get my hair done. i'm random and silly, but i am always loving & giving and always call a spade a spade.  i don't pretend to be someone i'm not. i am who i am, you can love me or hate me. and if i love you, i do it with all my heart!! i make no apologies for being who i am or for who i like or love and for that matter who i don't. if you judge me that's your business, i shall never judge you â¤ if you choose to not be in my life because of any choice or decision, good or bad that i make, i will respect your decision but i will never change my mind because of it 
#healyourself #beproud #beyou #lovemyself #iamstrong #day1 #skinnycownz #metoo

text:
over the next two weeks, we'll be tackling complex ptsd: what it is, how it compares to ptsd, and the infinite effects it can have on trauma survivors throughout their lives. we look forward to answering your questions and being about to offer additional support and resources where possible!
.
ğŸ’œğŸ’›ğŸ’œ
.
âœ§part 1âœ§
while not formally recognized in the dsm-5 yet, complex ptsd has been a term adopted by clinicians to describe the distinct differences between ptsd and the more complex, intricately woven effects of traumas of much longer duration and severity. complex ptsd carries its own set of projected criteria that we'll be describing in detail throughout the series. some of these criteria include things that may sound confusing at first - terms like emotional regulation, unstable perception of self as well as one's perpetrator, changes in consciousness, alterations in one's system of meanings, and more. so, if those things are unfamiliar to you, you will want to stay tuned as we walk you through them!
.
it should be noted that, while complex ptsd can develop at any age (unlike other dissociative trauma disorders, like did, which is early-childhood specific), crimes against children tend to result in c-ptsd more frequently. children are not only in a critical place in their emotional and self development, they are also more likely to feel powerless, as if they have no control, and there's no hope of getting free. because of this, complex ptsd is often discussed in terms of childhood trauma - however, that is not always the case! it absolutely can occur in teens and adulthood, particularly in recurrent trauma that's quite severe in nature -- most commonly, domestic violence.
.
given that october is #domesticviolenceawarenessmonth, it was especially important to bring more attention to complex ptsd now.
.

.
.
.
.
.

it just arrived a few minutes ago. i practically knock the ups driver down. he could not get back in his truck fast enough. actually i just thanked him about 10 times. i was sitting outside waiting. i was prepared to wait until 8 p.m. but he told me that he never stays out that long. so i'm glad to hear that because it was starting to get a bit chilly. anyway i've been looking through it and it's really and truly wonderful. for instance there's a page that talks about the muslim ban and right next to it is a picture of president obama greeting a group of kids from an islamic school in baltimore. my town. this one little girl has braces on her teeth and she is just looking at him with such affection the way he's looking at them. how did we go from such a kind man well read and well-educated. thoughtful articulate reasonable and open-minded. to you know who .... i'd actually rather speak voldemort's name. if you have the money to spare, give yourself this wonderful gift because it will lift your spirits and help you to remember that once we had a president. and then get out there and vote.

text:
women's sexuality and sexual expression has been under persecution from the patriarchy for millenia. even today, as women we experience shame, embarrassment and neglect of our sexuality. things like our monthly bleed, our sexual pleasure, the number of partners we have, orgasms, masturbation, and even how we birth has become taboo, controlled and contained! 
when a woman owns her sexual expression, she is an unstoppable force that doesn't put up with any shit. so its no wonder that in 1486, a book was published to put a stop to women's sexuality. the malleus maleficarum (aka the witchhunter's manual) was published. at the time, the religious powers really pushed the idea that good christian women were sexually vulnerable beings...easy prey for the devil. this is an actual quote from the book that was so popular, only the bible out-sold it!

actual quote: "what else is a women but a foe to friendship? they are evil, lecherous, vain and lustful. all witchcraft comes from carnal lust, which in women is insatiable." i had to look up what lecherous meant :Â having or showing excessive or offensive sexual desire.

wow. just another reason for this witch revolution. taking back the word witch means we take back our sexuality!! who is with me!?!?#iamwitch

text:
was that sexual harassment? how to create healthy workplaces. please join allegra fishel & a diverse group of organizations & presenters on this free webinar.
thursday, 3--4pm et. register at: https://tiny.cc/now1018 confused about what constitutes sexual harassment and what doesnâ€™t? do you want to do the right thing, but unsure of how to proceed? are you wondering if the #metoo movement means that any romantic relationship at work is automatically considered sexual harassment?
during this webinar, national experts will explain the nuances of sexual harassment in layman terms.
attorneys and advocates will also describe tools and tips to create harassment-free cultures in diverse settings.
---what are the additional considerations when the victim is a woman of color or gender nonconforming? ---what if the victim is undocumented?
learn how to go beyond legal requirements to create cultures where every employee is treated with respect, and therefore better performing. q&a afterward.

text:
#weshallbeheardâ¤ï¸
â€œmy #weshallbeheard story... the past few weeks have been very hard for me. listening to the testimony, i went through many emotions as has been the case over the past few years. i was sexually assaulted in a medical facility on thanksgiving day. it will be 4 years this coming thanksgiving. he took so much from me including thanksgiving day itself, as i have not celebrated since. it is always so hard for woman to have the courage to come forward with their story, just to be shot down and questioned. i chose to report it right away and even though it's been years, he has never lost his job. the message that that sends to me is it's okay for even a medical professional to do this. every detail of my life has been questioned. i have nothing in my past that i am at all ashamed of.  i havenâ€™t done anything to deserve his criminal act against me and then to be violated again by the questions they ask. what i have done or not done in my life is my business. this was never okay with me, and i was unconscious. even the detective seemed annoyed when he got the call and had to come to the police department early on thanksgiving morning to take my statement. he felt the need to tell me at least three times! it felt like he wanted me to know i shouldnâ€™t have interrupted his day with family while no one cared about mine. my fight continues.." #womensmarchonphiladelphia #metoo #wmop #wmo2019 #weshallbeheardstory #weshallbeheard #nomore #yourvoicehaspower #yourvoicematters #ibelieveyou #believesurvivors #actvism #marchforyourrights #feminist #werise #womenpowerment #speakingmytruth #powertothepolls #phillywomenrally

â€œmy #weshallbeheard story... the past few weeks have been very hard for me. listening to the testimony, i went through many emotions as has been the case over the past few years. i was sexually assaulted in a medical facility on thanksgiving day. it will be 4 years this coming thanksgiving. he took so much from me including thanksgiving day itself, as i have not celebrated since. it is always so hard for woman to have the courage to come forward with their story, just to be shot down and questioned. i chose to report it right away and even though it is been years, he has never lost his job. the message that that sends to me is it is okay for even a medical professional to do this. every detail of my life has been questioned. i have nothing in my past that i am at all ashamed of.  i havenâ€™t done anything to deserve his criminal act against me and then to be violated again by the questions they ask. what i have done or not done in my life is my business. this was never okay with me, and i was unconscious. even the detective seemed annoyed when he got the call and had to come to the police department early on thanksgiving morning to take my statement. he felt the need to tell me at least three times! it felt like he wanted me to know i shouldnâ€™t have interrupted his day with family while no one cared about mine. my fight continues.." #womensmarchonphiladelphia #metoo #wmop #wmo2019 #weshallbeheardstory #weshallbeheard #nomore #yourvoicehaspower #yourvoicematters #ibelieveyou #believesurvivors #actvism #marchforyourrights #feminist #werise #womenpowerment #speakingmytruth #powertothepolls #phillywomenrally

.
many attendees have groped me during pictures. cosplayers have followed me around, trying to get into my area of personal space, obviously coming on to me and making me feel uncomfortable and followed, even though i made it clear i wanted to lose them/was not at all interested. photographers have thought itâ€™s okay to say things in an overt sexual tone about me in front of my boyfriend. about me. iâ€™ve also had photographers touch my body or greet me in ways they think is okay because they â€œknow meâ€ and we are â€œfriendsâ€. (obviously @cflo.tography is not included in this because she is an angel, and if you want to shoot with an amazing photographer who always ensures youâ€™re comfortable and feel safe, she is the one!! â¤ï¸â¤ï¸)
.
my cosplays are my choice. no matter how revealing they are, no matter which character i am, no matter how long or short my skirt/shorts are, you are not allowed to touch me without my consent. or follow me around the event and make me feel uncomfortable. or say overtly sexual things to me.
.
this movement is very important to me, and itâ€™s important to me that people are safe. if you feel unsafe or recognize youâ€™re in an unsafe situation, please reach out to convention/event security. theyâ€™re there to help! if that might not be an option, or you donâ€™t feel comfortable, pull a friend aside and explain the situation. if you guys ever see me at a con and youâ€™re in an uncomfortable situation and arenâ€™t sure what to do, even if we have never met before, please come up to me. pretend you know me, and if you can, secretively tell me whatâ€™s going on. i will help you in any way i can. .
